tic materials have played a significant role in the historical deterioration of the statue[7](https://www.hallofmaat.com/sphinx/deterioration-of-the-stone-of-the-great-sphinx/).\n*   **Fossil Content:** The stone is also characterized by the presence of fossils, such as *Operculina pyramidum*, particularly in the harder, more durable layers used for the head of the Sphinx[6](https://gizamedia.rc.fas.harvard.edu/documents/lehner_diss_1991.pdf), [9](https://geoexpro.com/the-great-sphinx-of-egypt-natures-shabby-chic-trick/)."
